nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(neighbourhood_group) %>% 
  summarise(mean_price=mean(price),mean_avalibility=mean(availability_365))
## # A tibble: 5  3
##   neighbourhood_group mean_price mean_avalibility
##   <chr>                    <dbl>            <dbl>
## 1 Bronx                     82.8             214.
## 2 Brooklyn                 120.              132.
## 3 Manhattan                180.              123.
## 4 Queens                    94.7             179.
## 5 Staten Island            128.              212.
nyc_airbnb %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=price,y=availability_365,colour = neighbourhood_group))+
  geom_point()

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(neighbourhood_group,room_type) %>% 
  summarise(mean_price=mean(price)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=room_type,y=mean_price,colour = neighbourhood_group))+geom_point()+facet_grid(~neighbourhood_group)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'neighbourhood_group'. You can override
## using the `.groups` argument.

nyc_airbnb %>%
  filter(neighbourhood_group=="Manhattan",price<1000  ) %>% 
  slice(1:10) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  addTiles() %>% 
  addMarkers(~lat,~long)
